{
  "texts": [
    "Virtue ethics, with a focus on developing desirable character traits (virtues), has been studied in computing education as a way of, e.g., developing professional values [15].",
    "Care ethics (a feminist approach), focused on relationships instead of universal principles [16], is needed in engineering [35] and in computing in particular [30].",
    "Deontology, where the emphasis is on following universal rules, can be seen in engineering and computing in our agreement to follow the codes of ethics of professional organizations like ACM [1] and IEEE [18].",
    "The Group AssignmentThe course had two seminars on ethics in computing.",
    "During the first seminar, students were introduced to the awareness and responsibility part of the ethical process."
  ]
}